review_blob: Pours burnt honey colour, fizzy head quickly dissipated, medium dry bitterness with some cloying, quite dominating. Lack of hop flavour, all bitterness. Lack of malt presence.
If I wanted to drink something that tasted like this, I could have gone to the supermarket and bought a bottle of Cottees Chocolate Topping. But hey, at least it got me drunk.

not a bad beer, yet not as good as their pale. toned down version with far more subtle hop presence, filtered which seems to have stripped away potential character. still better than most and possesses a uniqueness. should make a nice summer beer if they make it more reasonably priced... ($60 slab @ dan murphys)
excellent beer. drank slightly chilled, cold winters night, great. alluring aroma.. drank from bottle so void of appearance. strong beer yet alcohol masked well. pleasant afterthoughts.
standard issue beer, most common on tap around these parts. not much character, but does the job. consistent performer.
boring, just like water. lack of any quality aspects of aroma or flavor. citrus makes it worthwhile....
